# DataBase design - YapHub
This is a database model a simple media platform where a user/users can create posts and upload them and follow other users.

##Entities

### Users
The Users entity is where the information is stored about each of every user on the platform.

Attributes:
- user_id - unique identifier for each user
- username - unique username
- password_hash - hashed password for authentication in the login
- first_name - user's first name
- last_name - user's last name
- birthday - users date of birth

----------

### Posts
The posts entity is where the content is stored when the user creates one.

Attributes:
- post_id - unique identifier for each post
- content - the text section for the post
- created_at - a timestamp of when the post was made
- expires_at - a timestamp of the expiration

--------

RelationShips 

### Writes 
The Writes relationship is connected users and posts.

- One User can write many posts
- Each post is then written by ONE user

this is where the one to many relationship comes from.

Foreign key:
- post,user_id connects to User, user_id.

----------

### Follows
The follows relationship is a self made relationship from the entity 'users'.
- User can follow 'many' users
- User can be followed by 'many' users

These are then stroed into the Follows table inn the relational schema where ypu can see i posted an image of 


----------

